laboratory_examinations.findings: Multisegmental thick perivenous sheathing which might indicate vasculitis.
Deposits at the disrupted ellipsoid zone in the left eye.
Temporal hemianopia of the left eye.
Multiple serpiginous signal-void channels at the retrobulbar region of the left orbit with probable compression on the left ophthalmic nerve.

Total occlusion of the horizontal cavernous segment of the left internal carotid artery (ICA) with collaterals from the left ophthalmic artery. Total occlusion of the terminal segment of the right ICA with collaterals from the right ophthalmic artery.
Prominent collaterals around the optic canal compressing the optic nerve.
